</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:16
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='485933' id='t-485933'>So now you may ask</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='488504' id='t-488504'>why children's lies
are so difficult to detect.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='492958' id='t-492958'>Let me illustrate this
with my own son, Nathan.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='495994' id='t-495994'>This is his facial expression</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='498187' id='t-498187'>when he lies.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:30
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='499595' id='t-499595'>(Laughter)</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:32
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='501825' id='t-501825'>So when children lie,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='503451' id='t-503451'>their facial expression
